<br>
I'm not going to do another Suze vs. Jochan battle.  My choices not only speak for themselves, but I have already elaborated why they are superior.<br>
<br>
This thread is about the &quot;optimal&quot; path or paths for a magician.  My theory is that efficiency is the most optimal path.  You can argue roleplay reasons, you can argue about kill rate (and by the way, you are wrong.  Without subsidizing your evoc tactics with heavy doses of FT and clarity buffs, the chainer will come out the exp winner in most any zone, vs most any mobs.)  You can argue about virtually anything you want, but you can't easily argue against efficiency.  Efficiency allows you to kill more in a given amount of time by reducing or eliminating downtime.  Once you are at the point where downtime is eliminated, you can add more evocation style tactics (i.e. more nukes/rains) to reduce kill time as well.<br>
<br>
Pet Discipline is useful and helpful in a variety of circumstances, but it does very little for efficiency.  As such it is a lower priority than Spell Casting Mastery, for example.  Subtlety has its merits as well, in groups, raids, and solo, but once again it's doubtful it should take a higher priority than, say, Spell Casting Fury.<br>
<br>
Once again, when you reach a point where you have maximized efficiency in a variety of tactics, the rest is all personal tastes, or special needs.<br>
<br>
Incidentally...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Summoning and killing a pet<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
... is not what Reclaim Energy is about.  It's about recouping mana costs involved in transporting an elemental pet from the planes from which they come.  Pets don't die when reclaimed, they return/despawn and leave energy to be absorbed.  They die when the mob beats them down to 0 hit points.  Expert magicians have discovered how to harness reclaim in such an efficient way that they can reclaim more energy than they spent to summon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suzannadreamingheart>SuzannaDreamingheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Evocation</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 2:30:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Optimal AA path for magicians</span><hr size=1> ======<br>
